The paper presents a deep learning framework for object co-segmentation, which is a task related to computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves unsupervised learning and supervised image classification, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed model uses multi-resolution image features, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and image retrieval (cs.IR) research.
